reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for kids!
reviews.reviewText: I used these cubes to pack my kids’ vacation clothes all in one bag. I have 3 kids (ages 9/8/6) and used one cube for each of their clothes on multiple back-to-back 4-day vacations. When we arrive at the hotel, they keep their own bag by their bed and dirty clothes immediately go into the suitcase which allowed for everything to stay organized without mixing clean and dirty laundry.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Compact for packing. Great spacesaver and organizer.
reviews.reviewText: Star added and update 7/1/2023: I used these on a month-long trip. We stayed in most locations only two nights. These spared me so many headaches! It was easy to reach in and grab what I needed without rifling through and messing up the whole suitcase. I packed hiking pants in one bag, jeans and regular pants in another, t-shirts in the third, and winter gear (scarf, gloves, hats, thick socks, etc.) in the last one. It was so efficient that I just ordered more packing cubes today! Even though they weren't compressible (because they're mesh), it took up way less room in the suitcase because I could squeeze everything in the bag, so the only space was between bags and not between every article of clothing (if that makes sense). I rolled everything, not folded.I forgot to count how many t-shirts I got in a bag, but I went back to look at pictures. It was more than 10 because I had 2 long-sleeved silkies packed and pictures wearing 8 different tees, and I didn't wear them all. At least three of the tees were long-sleeved in addition to the silkies. Two of the long-sleeved ones were size large so I could layer other shirts under them. So each cube holds a good amount of clothing! I had at least 5 pairs of jeans and pants in one, including one pair of very wide-leg, high-waisted jeans.The fabric held up well on this trip. I didn't have trouble with the zippers. Hopefully they will continue to hold up and perform well. Very pleased!************Original review:I’m going to have to pack these with my t-shirts and see how many fit. It looks like it won’t hold nearly as many shirts as pictured, but I’ll see. I wear a women’s small, and I would be surprised if I could get even 6 t-shirts to fit as smoothly as that picture.I was worried they would be too big to be efficient for packing, but they aren’t. I think a happy medium could have been found, but we’ll see how it goes. I definitely am leaving one empty for dirties. (I like that better than my solid nylon bag for dirties — no breathing for the dirty clothes. Ick.)They are very thin and light, which is good for packing, but they feel almost flimsy. I’ll see how they hold up with packing and will update my review with that information and a picture! 😊

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Packing cubes are a game changer
reviews.reviewText: I've seen like a bazillion articles and reviews going on and on and on about the virtues of packing cubes and I thought it was just a money making gimmick for the longest time.THEY were right, I was wrong.They make everything easier. When I travel, I army roll/ranger roll all my clothes then arrange them in the suitcase. With these, I can put t-shirts together, underwear and socks together, dressy clothes together, etc. PLUS I seem to be able to get even more clothes in a suitcase without cramming using these than without.Aside from organizing clothes before a trip, they come in handy during travels, so you can put dirty laundry in it's own bag to keep them from ruining clean clothes, as well as holding shoes, sandals, toiletries, cables and chargers, etc. They are the best for organizing things.I don't consider these to be flimsy or cheap at all. If you're looking to conserve space, you don't want added bulk or weight. They're strong enough to pack tightly, the zippers are strong, and the mesh top allows you to see what's inside each cube.I am a convert and now I never pack and travel without my packing cubes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are the best and I can't believe I lived without them!
reviews.reviewText: These arrived just in time for my trip, and I can’t believe I ever packed without them. I am a master at packing and had no idea how much I needed packing cubes in my life!There’s nothing worse than having to use several packing bags because just one is too small… But at 12” long, 9” wide and 5” deep, these are large enough for almost any of your needs (one guy on the plane looked like he could’ve been carrying one of these as a carry-on)!These have a million uses but I find they make wonderful toiletry bags when you’re traveling. One is large enough to hold all your toiletries, helping me to stay organized, without having to dig through my luggage to find what I’m looking for. These can also hold your shoes, several outfits, electronics, and a ton more; and not just when you’re traveling, but even at home. And the price, especially for these well-made bags, is a steal at $20 for a 4pk!Another great thing about them is the transparent mesh, allowing you to see what you have packed without having to open it up and fish around. It has a handle, double zippers and the material & stitchwork is of a high quality; they seem rugged enough to hold up for years.I can’t believe I didn’t know about that packing cube life. I’m mad no one told me I needed these… so I’m telling you: get them. They’re awesome.
